    "body": "So I want to respond to people's messages like this\r\n```\r\nfunction onGetMessage($mynumber, $from, $id, $type, $time, $name, $body)\r\n{\r\n\t$text = trim($body);\r\n\tif(substr($text, 0, 1) == '!') {\r\n\t\t$text = substr($text, 1);\r\n\t\tswitch($text) {\r\n\t\t\tcase 'time':\r\n\t\t\t\t$w->sendMessage($from, time());\r\n\t\t\t\tbreak;\r\n\t\t\tdefault:\r\n\t\t\t\t$w->sendMessage($from, 'Invalid command. Use !commands for a list of commands.');\r\n\t\t\t\tbreak;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\n//Create the whatsapp object and setup a connection.\r\n$w = new WhatsProt($username, $identity, $nickname, $debug);\r\n$w->connect();\r\n\r\n// Now loginWithPassword function sends Nickname and (Available) Presence\r\n$w->loginWithPassword($password);\r\n\r\n$w->eventManager()->bind(\"onGetMessage\", \"onGetMessage\");\r\n\r\n//update your profile picture\r\n$w->sendSetProfilePicture(\"demo/venom.jpg\");\r\n\r\n$w->sendStatusUpdate('(c) 2013 Sydcul');\r\n\r\nwhile(true)\r\n{\r\n    $w->PollMessages();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut when I run this script from the command line it gives me this\r\n```\r\nPHP Notice:  Undefined variable: w in /home/sydcul/WhatsAPI-master/src/php/test1.php on line 42\r\nPHP Fatal error:  Call to a member function sendMessage() on a non-object in /home/sydcul/WhatsAPI-master/src/php/test1.php on line 42\r\n```\r\n\r\nLine 42 is the function where it is supposed to send the message\r\n```\r\n$w->sendMessage($from, 'Invalid command. Use !commands for a list of commands.');\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt does not give me this error when I use sendMessage outside of a function.",
